"Overview
  • General Information
  • Requirements for use
  • Setup of oblify
  • Notification Central
  • Administration Area
  • Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)
General Information

oblify is a context-aware reminder system. This means it observes the status of common devices which are registered at oblify system and notifies the user if the device finished its procedure. The outgoing notification will be sent to the user in the smartest way depending by the current situation. For example if the user sits in front of his computer the oblify system knows that and will send the notification to that screen.
Scenario: Bob recently installed the oblify system at home. Now he wants to vent his living room. For this he opens the window. Afterwards he wants to cook in the kitchen. While he is cooking the weather is going to get rainy. Because the oblify system detected that Bob opened the window and also checked the weather data the system recognizes and notifies him that he should close the window in the living room. Because Bob is currently in the kitchen and only his smartphone is nearby, so oblify generates a notification to Bob\ufffds phone.

back to overview

Requirements for use

For using oblify a few requirements are necessary. First oblify app needs to be connected constantly via WiFi to the home network where oblify server is running. If WiFi connection gets lost the app is not usable anymore and changes to connecting screen. Second, the app uses Bluetooth instantly for locating other Bluetooth-devices registered in the system and useful for notification outputs. So it is necessary to switch on Bluetooth on the smartphone where oblify is running. If Bluetooth is deactivated all notifications will always be sent to the app instead of other sensible output devices.

back to overview

Setup of oblify

oblify is very simple to install. Please use the following steps for the setup.

  1. Connect the server application to your home network and start the server.
  2. Put a power meter between each device and its power socket. Additionally put all window sensors on the desired windows.

back to overview

Notification Central

The Notification Central is the heart of oblify app. In this notifications which were generated by other devices will be shown in this area. The oblify server generates that notification and sends it to the app. All incoming notifications are red-colored that means they are unread for the system. For an acknowledgment that the notification is noticed by user it is necessary to click the notification in the list. The color chances to green and the system knows the message was read and can handle that.
Moreover the notifications will be sent in a smart way. Depending from users situation and smartphone profile incoming notifications can be soundless, vibrating or with a speech.

back to overview

Administration Area

In this area all devices integrated in oblify system can be monitored. It is possible to get their current status, to activate and deactivate them. So if it is not desired to get notifications of particular devices there they can be deactivated for the oblify system. The access to this area requires the input of a password.

back to overview

Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)
